        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 2:16AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 216 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Barnett Shoals, or near
Watkinsville, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail, frequent cloud
to ground lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Watkinsville, Lexington, Crawford, Arnoldsville, Bishop, Maxeys,
Rayle, Whitehall, Athens-Clarke County, Stephens, Jacksons
Crossroads, Hutchings, Barnett Shoals, Newtown, State Botanical
Garden Of Ga, Celeste, Philomath, Vesta, Farmington, and Carters
Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
